 control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705201,"age":95,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Hanna Lacy was born in 1454, in Devon, England. She had at least 1 son with John Gilbert. She died in 1555, in England, at the age of 101, and was buried in Bristol, Gloucestershire, England."},"et":{"1454–1555":"1454–1555","1450–1494":"1450–1494","1455–1539":"1455–1539","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1 May 1539":"1. mai 1539","1555":"1555","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","28 October 1759":"28. oktoober 1759","1475":"1475","1494":"1494","1450":"1450","about 1475":"umbes 1475","2 February 1494":"2. veebruar 1494","1539":"1539","1549":"1549","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England","England":"England","Bridgwater, Somerset, England":"Bridgwater, Somerset, England","St. George, Bristol, Gloucester, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","Compton, Devon, England":"Compton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1454–1555":"1454–1555","1450–1494":"1450–1494","1455–1539":"1455–1539","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","1 May 1539":"1. toukokuuta 1539","1555":"1555","1455":"1455","1454":"1454","28 October 17